Great, relaxing, challenging game. No ads or in app purchases. Developer has been active, adding new levels, though it looks like there won't be any more.

1) Large number of beautiful & inventive courses, altho sometimes either too easy or too frustratingly gimmicky. 2) Simple, easy swing dynamic which can prove a bit annoying due to the 'wandering bullseye' feature. 3) FWIW-- hook & slice are missing, and there's no club choices. 4) Game could really use an option to pan around each hole before playing. 5) Putting doesn't have much nuance to it. The slopes of the greens have little real effect, and most putts are either too easy to make (just aim straight) or impossible (ball won't travel far enough). SUMMARY: Fun game, yes, but also feels flawed and unfinished. Last point-- it's too easy to unlock all the starred features, and the bonus features (like green pumpkins) aren't explained at all.

content: An amazing amount of content packed into a small premium package. The low-poly look reminds me a bit of Hitman GO, though less "tabletop aesthetic," and the courses have interesting hole layouts. Controls are simple enough for what the game is--getting three stars on all courses will be challenging, but it's definitely possible. I've noticed that from Hawaii onward, the physics are cranked up a bit on some later courses--maybe to up the difficulty--leading to balls conveniently rolling down into sand traps and water hazards from inclines that would normally have less effect on the ball. I'd rather the physics be consistent all around. Also, if the ball is obscured by trees or other obstacles, the outline of the ball is shown, but the objects in the way don't become transparent, making it difficult to line up shots at that point. Despite these minor issues, the game is still great overall. Lots of replay value in going for better scores, playing the other game modes, finding hidden holes, etc. Also, for anyone experiencing the recent glitch where nothing happens after the ball goes into a hole, just uninstall and reinstall the app. Easy fix.

I don't understand the negative reviews for this game. It's a great game. Simple controls, looks great (pics don't do it justice), reasonably good on batteries, ~99 holes to play (haven't actually counted), and the "music" is relaxing. In response to other stupid reviews. Physics are fine. It's entirely possible to get birdies. Par is usually pretty simple to get and birdies require slightly more thought. And you can shoot through trees where is makes sense to. This is definitely a casual game, so don't expect overly difficult gameplay. There are some camera issues in regards to trees, but this effects maybe 2-3 (out of ~99) holes and it's not a problem for the rest of the game. There is nice variation between courses. And, as said earlier, they look really cool. I was really surprised by how much I liked this game. Replay value is fairly small, but you get a ton of good holes to play. Either way, simple, looks good, and fun.

content: THE BAD: A) Dynamics are off. I don't play games I win games. I played the championship's first 3 courses 14 times, trying to advance with three stars each time, but I realized that the slopes don't work like they are supposed to. B) The hole is RIGHT next to the start, and there is no way to get to it except the long way, causing me to strike 3-4 times each course. There should be a way to get over the trees and mountains. That's not fair. C) The game does not let the ball go in the hole if you get near it. It seems as it you have to putt it in every time unless you land it from the air. THE GOOD: A) Great game with good graphics. I like the single player aspect of it. B) No timer, it's a simple relaxing game. C) The environment is pretty. D) I like the secret holes and courses. E) I like the idea of FUTURE courses being added on. Fix the bad stuff, it's a great game. It's better than Golf Clash, Golf Rivals any of them. Please fix these bugs to make a great game amazing.

design choices and wonky physics. You only have two types of shots, and 
it's regular to a power shot. That's it, no flop, punch, or anything else. 
Simple, but when you match this with maps that would be great for these 
kinds of shots, it creates needless aggrivation. Doesn't help when the 
physics and hit detection is so bad that you will hit trees and literally 
get stuck on the sides of mountains, even when you are seemingly clear of 
them. Suffice to say I wish there was a better version of this game, I also 
wish there were refunds. Also the camera needs work and I don't have a clue 
where they came up with the par scores for some of these holes.

Solid golf game.it has a pleasing geometric style, but the ground is quite varied and smooth. It is relaxing. The progression system is good. This game would benefit from a few things. The main thing is that it would be nice to switch between different clubs. Not clubs from real life, but a system that would be easy to understand, learning club names in other golf games is confusing, and it wouldn't fit with the other intuitive controls. Being able to use a normal hit on the green could prevent situations where you can't even get the ball into the hole at full power and you need to restart the whole level.  This game definitely knows what it wants to be, and it does a good job. Also, things like conveyors or fans would make the gameplay a little more interesting, but they wouldn't fit in with the rest of this game so I hope they might consider it for ok golf 2.

The fairway is ice (watch your ball roll 50 yards into the water) the rough is glue (the second it touches a pixel of it you can't hit farther than 10 yards), and the wind is a hurricane (when combined with the rough the ball literally lands in the same spot). Taking the fairway is almost never a good idea for getting three-stars (hence why I assume it's a puzzle game), and the best targets in each hole always seem to be placed in between the normal stroke and power shot.

content: Gorgeous game with great sound effects. Very relaxing!
Great golf game.  I wish it had at least 2 or 3 options to increase power or add spin. I've played this ALOT just how it is though.

Love the simple controls that make this such a good translation of golf to a mobile. Would love to see more complexity in the stroke mechanics as it relates to interactions with surfaces and contact with objects.  This would lead to less of a hunt for the perfect (and ultimately only) ball path.  Outside of that I love everything about this game. The pure focus on gameplay. The audio choices for background sound. The satisfying click sound of the club striking the ball. It's just that dun to play.

Great fun! Really enjoying it. Update: I don't know what's happened and if it is just me but after the update the button and ball hit/swipe detection are way off to the point where I seriously struggle to press the correct button.
